Western Slope Willow was born from a singular vision: that container design is not landscaping, it's living art.

Hannah brings over two decades of horticultural mastery and a formal degree from Oklahoma State to every composition she creates. Her container work has earned a reputation for breathtaking artistry, the kind of designs that stop you mid-stride, that guests photograph, that become the defining element of a property's first impression.

Where others see a pot and some plants, Hannah sees sculpture. Color theory. Seasonal drama. The interplay of texture, scale, and negative space. Each container is composed with the precision of a painter and the botanical knowledge of a scientist, designed not just to survive Colorado's demanding alpine environment, but to thrive in it.

Her understanding of high-altitude horticulture runs deep. The intense UV exposure, dramatic temperature swings, and abbreviated growing season at 9,000+ feet require expertise that simply can't be improvised. It comes from 20 years of hands-on study in this exact environment.

From our own greenhouse, we cultivate specialty plants and premium willow varieties that you won't find anywhere else, giving us the palette to create truly one-of-a-kind designs for clients who expect the extraordinary.

We're still a family operation at heart. You'll often find us working alongside our kids, dirt under our fingernails, doing what we love. But make no mistake: the work that leaves here belongs on the finest properties in the Rockies.

Our Offerings

Services & Plants

From bespoke design services to hand-grown specialty plants, everything is cultivated with care.

Bespoke Container Design

Our signature service. We create container gardens that transcend the ordinary, living sculptures that command attention and evolve beautifully through the seasons.

Each composition considers scale, architecture, exposure, and your aesthetic vision. From grand entrance urns to intimate balcony collections.

Request Consultation

Estate Horticultural Planning

Comprehensive botanical strategy for properties that demand more than landscaping. We develop cohesive planting schemes that enhance architecture, frame views, and create outdoor living spaces of distinction.

Our planning process begins with deep site analysis, understanding microclimates, soil conditions, and the property's relationship to the surrounding landscape.

Schedule Site Visit

Basketry & Specialty Willow

We cultivate dozens of willow varieties, each with unique colors, textures, and properties. Whether you need strong, flexible rods for basketry and weaving, fast-growing trees for a living fence, or ornamental varieties for your landscape.

All shipped dormant and ready to plant. Available through our online shops.
